  "BodyEn": "\u003Cdiv class=\u0022captioned-image-container\u0022\u003E\u003Cfigure\u003E\u003Ca class=\u0022image-link image2 is-viewable-img\u0022 target=\u0022_blank\u0022 href=\u0022https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!guLA!,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd37c51c4-68de-4567-b46b-54870b91e174_1080x1080.jpeg\u0022 data-component-name=\u0022Image2ToDOM\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022image2-inset\u0022\u003E\u003Cpicture\u003E\u003Csource type=\u0022image/webp\u0022 srcset=\u0022https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!guLA!,w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd37c51c4-68de-4567-b46b-54870b91e174_1080x1080.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!guLA!,w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd37c51c4-68de-4567-b46b-54870b91e174_1080x1080.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!guLA!,w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd37c51c4-68de-4567-b46b-54870b91e174_1080x1080.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!guLA!,w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd37c51c4-68de-4567-b46b-54870b91e174_1080x1080.jpeg 1456w\u0022 sizes=\u0022100vw\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!guLA!,w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd37c51c4-68de-4567-b46b-54870b91e174_1080x1080.jpeg\u0022 width=\u00221080\u0022 height=\u00221080\u0022 data-attrs=\u0022{\u0026quot;src\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/d37c51c4-68de-4567-b46b-54870b91e174_1080x1080.jpeg\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;srcNoWatermark\u0026quot;:null,\u0026quot;fullscreen\u0026quot;:null,\u0026quot;imageSize\u0026quot;:null,\u0026quot;height\u0026quot;:1080,\u0026quot;width\u0026quot;:1080,\u0026quot;resizeWidth\u0026quot;:null,\u0026quot;bytes\u0026quot;:125955,\u0026quot;alt\u0026quot;:null,\u0026quot;title\u0026quot;:null,\u0026quot;type\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;image/jpeg\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;href\u0026quot;:null,\u0026quot;belowTheFold\u0026quot;:false,\u0026quot;topImage\u0026quot;:true,\u0026quot;internalRedirect\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;https://rami13kh.substack.com/i/174425125?img=https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd37c51c4-68de-4567-b46b-54870b91e174_1080x1080.jpeg\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;isProcessing\u0026quot;:false,\u0026quot;align\u0026quot;:null,\u0026quot;offset\u0026quot;:false}\u0022 class=\u0022sizing-normal\u0022 alt=\u0022\u0022 srcset=\u0022https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!guLA!,w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd37c51c4-68de-4567-b46b-54870b91e174_1080x1080.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!guLA!,w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd37c51c4-68de-4567-b46b-54870b91e174_1080x1080.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!guLA!,w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd37c51c4-68de-4567-b46b-54870b91e174_1080x1080.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!guLA!,w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd37c51c4-68de-4567-b46b-54870b91e174_1080x1080.jpeg 1456w\u0022 sizes=\u0022100vw\u0022 fetchpriority=\u0022high\u0022\u003E\u003C/picture\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/figure\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003Cp\u003EImage by the author, the upper side image is from an entrepreneurship competition that happened in Syria in 2015. The downside is from my participation in a conference that happened in Dubai in 2024.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDisclaimer:\u003C/strong\u003E \u003Cem\u003EThis article was fully written by me without the use of AI tools. All thoughts, words, and ideas are my own.\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/figure\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe phrase \u201CIf you can\u2019t explain it simply, you don\u2019t understand it well enough\u201D is a\u003Cstrong\u003E \u003C/strong\u003Ewidely attributed quote to \u003Cstrong\u003EAlbert Einstein\u003C/strong\u003E, reflecting the idea that a deep understanding of a concept allows one to break it down into simple, understandable terms, and that complexity in explanation often stems from a lack of genuine comprehension.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E2- Since I mentioned teaching and mentoring, where can a person teach? There are a lot of organizations and NGOs, for example, Paper Airplanes - Free Online Education For Refugees (https://www.paper-airplanes.org), which is a great place to volunteer and help others.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E3- If you are thinking of doing a career shift to another field, but you\u2019re not sure if that field is the right one for you, and you have just a feeling that it\u2019s your passion, doing volunteer work would be a great way to find out.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIn 2017, I was doing freelance work, which involved doing research about the semantic web, and then I did a course in machine learning because my graduation project was about recommendation systems. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EI felt that I liked data science related fields, and I improved my knowledge about data analysis and statistics over  the years by doing courses or reading books from time to time. Later, and before I make any serious career shift (thankfully), I discovered through the steps that I\u2019ve mentioned, that liking something does not necessarily mean that it\u2019s my place.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThrough the steps that I\u2019ve mentioned: volunteering, teaching, mentoring, etc., you will gain experience, and you will find positive or negative answers to your questions, which will help you get over your doubts.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ELet me know what you think, and if you have other ways to gain experience in a domain beyond your career\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThanks for reading\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ERami\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022subscription-widget-wrap-editor\u0022 data-attrs=\u0022{\u0026quot;url\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;https://rami13kh.substack.com/subscribe?\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;text\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;Subscribe\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;language\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;en\u0026quot;}\u0022 data-component-name=\u0022SubscribeWidgetToDOM\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022subscription-widget show-subscribe\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022preamble\u0022\u003E\u003Cp class=\u0022cta-caption\u0022\u003EThanks for reading! Subscribe for free to receive new posts and support my work.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003Cform class=\u0022subscription-widget-subscribe\u0022\u003E\u003Cinput type=\u0022email\u0022 class=\u0022email-input\u0022 name=\u0022email\u0022 placeholder=\u0022Type your email\u2026\u0022 tabindex=\u0022-1\u0022\u003E\u003Cinput type=\u0022submit\u0022 class=\u0022button primary\u0022 value=\u0022Subscribe\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022fake-input-wrapper\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022fake-input\u0022\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022fake-button\u0022\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/form\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/div\u003E",
